thread.title: Copper Prices Fall After Weaker-Than-Expected Chinese Import Data
thread.title_full: Copper Prices Fall After Weaker-Than-Expected Chinese Import Data - WSJ

author: Biman Mukherji
title: Copper Prices Fall After Weaker-Than-Expected Chinese Import Data
text:
LONDON—Copper prices fell in tandem with other base metals on Tuesday after weaker-than-expected Chinese import data for September cast a pall over a recent price rebound from multiyear lows.
China’s overall imports fell 17.7% in yuan terms over the month, compared with a 14.3% decrease in August, government data showed Tuesday.
